  <!-- Benefits with hero-side image -->
  <section id="why-autos" class="grid cols-2">
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Why Autoflowers Are Great for First-Time Growers</h2>
      <ul class="pros">
        <li><strong>Short seed-to-harvest:</strong> many finish in <strong>8–12 weeks</strong>. Faster feedback = faster learning.</li>
        <li><strong>Compact:</strong> ideal for <strong>2×2 or 3×3 tents</strong>, closets, or cabinets.</li>
        <li><strong>Simple lighting:</strong> run <code>18/6</code> or <code>20/4</code> the whole grow—no 12/12 flip needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Budget friendly:</strong> smaller gear and lower power draw.</li>
        <li><strong>Staggered harvests:</strong> pop a new seed every 3–4 weeks for steady jars.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout">Because autos aren’t triggered by a strict dark period, you can grow them almost anywhere—bedroom corner, utility room, or shop—so long as you maintain <strong>airflow</strong>, <strong>temperature</strong>, and <strong>humidity</strong>.</div>
      <div class="chips">
        <span class="chip">Beginner Safe</span><span class="chip">Low Fuss</span><span class="chip">Small Space</span>
      </div>
    </article>
    <aside class="panel">
      <figure class="card">
