  <!-- Setup split with tent shots floated right -->
  <section id="setup" class="grid cols-2">
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Simple Setup That Works (Without Going Broke)</h2>
      <h3>Core Gear</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tent:</strong> 2×2 or 3×3 (or <strong>4×4</strong> if you want headroom & expansion).</li>
        <li><strong>Light:</strong> 150–250W full-spectrum LED, safe distance per PPFD chart.</li>
        <li><strong>Air:</strong> 6″ inline fan + carbon filter, plus a small oscillating fan inside.</li>
        <li><strong>Containers:</strong> 3–5 gal fabric pots with light, airy soil.</li>
        <li><strong>Water & pH:</strong> Soil pH 6.0–6.5 (coco 5.8–6.2). Water slowly; let pots lighten.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="callout">Pro move: Use final pots from the start to avoid transplant shock. Autos dislike delays.</p>
      <div class="chips"><span class="chip">Quiet Fan</span><span class="chip">Carbon Filter</span><span class="chip">Timer</span><span class="chip">Hygrometer</span></div>
    </article>
